Function Reference/user can « WordPress Codex
-----------

Whether a user has capability or role. Similar to
[current\_user\_can()](/Function_Reference/current_user_can "Function Reference/current user can"),
but this function takes a user ID or object as its first parameter.

Usage
-----

`  <?php user_can( $user, $capability ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$user` 
:   ([*object or integer
    (ID)*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Object_or_integer_.28ID.29 "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) required
    Default: *None*

 `$capability` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*)
    [capability](/Roles_and_Capabilities "Roles and Capabilities") or
    role name.
    Default: *None*

Returns
-------

 (boolean) 
:   user has capability or role.

Changelog
---------

Since: [Version 3.1](/Version_3.1 "Version 3.1")

Source Code
-----------

`user_can()` is located in `wp-includes/capabilities.php`.

